         <div xml:id="bHY6yh-d78990"><!-- p4l3-r8 -->
            <head xml:id="bHY6yh-d78990-Hd1e108">Rubrica 8</head>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d78990-d1e111">
               <lb ed="#V" n="28"/>
      ¶ De terribilitate et metu. Rubrica. 8.
    </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d78990-d1e116">
               <lb ed="#V" n="29"/> <ref>SAlomon in prouerbiis c. 15</ref>
      <lb ed="#V" n="30"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d78990-Qd1e122">Secura mens
        <lb ed="#V" n="31"/>quasi iuge conuiuium.</quote> 
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d78990-d1e128"> 
          <ref>/ 20. c.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d78990-Qd1e130">Sicui
        <lb ed="#V" n="32"/>T rugitus leonis: ita et terror regis: qui
        <lb ed="#V" n="33"/>prouocat eum peccat in animam suam.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d78990-d1e138">
               <lb ed="#V" n="34"/>
                <ref>¶ Cronica de nugis philosophorum. c. 4 scilice
        <lb ed="#V" n="35"/>de chilione.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d78990-Qd1e142">Chilo lacedemonius: qui fuit vnus
        <lb ed="#V" n="36"/>de septem sapiententibus iubebat mansuetum
        <lb ed="#V" n="37"/>esse: vt proximi reuereantur magisquam timeant.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d78990-d1e153">
               <lb ed="#V" n="38"/>
                <ref>¶ Aristotelis ethincorum: li. 3. c. 7.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d78990-Qd1e157">Terribilissi
        <lb ed="#V" n="39"/>mum est mors. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d78990-d1e163"> 
          <ref>/ Idem pollyticorum: li. 5.
        <lb ed="#V" n="40"/>c. 3</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d78990-Qd1e165">Congregat etiam separatissimos com
        <lb ed="#V" n="41" break="no"/>munis timor.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d78990-d1e173">
               <lb ed="#V" n="42"/>
             <ref>¶ Terentius in adelphis. c. 3. </ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d78990-Qd1e177">Pudore et li
        <lb ed="#V" n="43" break="no"/>beralitate liberos
        <lb ed="#V" n="44"/>Retinere satius esse credo quam metu
        <lb ed="#V" n="45"/>Qui imperium credat grauius aut stabilius <!--236.xml-->
        <cb ed="#V" n="b"/>
                  <lb ed="#V" n="46"/>Ui quod sit quam illud quod amicitia adiungitur.
        <lb ed="#V" n="47"/>Malo coactus qui suum officium facit
        <lb ed="#V" n="48"/>Dum id rescitum iri credit tuntisper cauet
        <lb ed="#V" n="49"/>Si sperat fore clam rursum ad ingenium redit.  
         <lb ed="#V" n="50"/>Ille quem beneficio adiungas ex aninio facit.
        <lb ed="#V" n="51"/>Studet par referre: pomitus absensque. idem erit
        <lb ed="#V" n="52"/>Hoc patrum est potius consnefacere filium.
        <lb ed="#V" n="53"/>Sua sponte recte facere quam alieno metu. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d78990-d1e214">
               <lb ed="#V" n="54"/> <ref>¶ Tullius phylipicorum: lib. i.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d78990-Qd1e218">Metui et ob
        <lb ed="#V" n="55"/>id odiosum esse inuidiosum est detestabile
        <lb ed="#V" n="56"/>imbecillum caducum. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d78990-d1e226">
               <lb ed="#V" n="57"/>
               <ref>¶ Ouidius de fasti: li. 4.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d78990-Qd1e230">Excutitur terrore quies </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d78990-d1e235">
               <lb ed="#V" n="58"/>
            <ref>¶ Seneca tragediarum in hercule furente. c.
        <lb ed="#V" n="59"/>3.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d78990-Qd1e239">Oppmit leges timor.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d78990-d1e245"> 
          <ref>/ In octauia. c. 10</ref>
        <lb ed="#V" n="60"/> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d78990-Qd1e247">Decet timeri cesarem: At plus diligi. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d78990-d1e253">
               <lb ed="#V" n="61"/>
               <ref>/ Idem epistolarum ad lucillum: lib. 18. e. 5.</ref>
        <lb ed="#V" n="62"/> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d78990-Qd1e257">Timeri tam domi quam foris molestum est: tam
        <lb ed="#V" n="63"/>a seruis quam a liberis. Nemo potest terribilis
        <lb ed="#V" n="64"/>esse secure.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d78990-d1e267"> 
         <ref>/ Idem de ira: li. 2.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d78990-Qd1e269"> Periculosius
        <lb ed="#V" n="65"/>est timeri quam despici. Necesse est vt multos ti
        <lb ed="#V" n="66"/>meat quem multi timent.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d78990-d1e277">
               <lb ed="#V" n="67"/>
               <ref>¶ Lex dig. ti. quod metns causa etc. l. i.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d78990-Qd1e281">Metus
        <lb ed="#V" n="68"/>instantis vel futuri priculi causa metus trepidatio</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d78990-d1e287">
               <lb ed="#V" n="69"/>
             <ref>¶ Macrobius saturnaliorum: li. 2. c. 7.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d78990-Qd1e291">Co
        <lb ed="#V" n="70"/>lant te potius serui tui quam timeant: qui coli
        <lb ed="#V" n="71" break="no"/>tur etiam amatur. Non potest amor cum ti
        <lb ed="#V" n="72"/>more minsceri</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d78990-d1e302"> 
          <ref>/ 18 c. exautior liberii:</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d78990-Qd1e304">Ne
        <lb ed="#V" n="73" break="no"/>cesse est multos timeat quem multi timent. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d78990-d1e310">
               <lb ed="#V" n="74"/>
             <ref>¶ Cassiodorus epistolarum: li. 2. e. 5.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d78990-Qd1e314">Solus
        <lb ed="#V" n="75"/>metus cohibm quos fides promissi non retiet.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d78990-d1e320">
               <lb ed="#V" n="76"/>
               <ref>¶ Claudianus: li. 3</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d78990-Qd1e324">Non odium terrore moues.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d78990-d1e328">
               <lb ed="#V" n="77"/>
         <ref>¶ Gregorius in pastorali. c. 38.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d78990-Qd1e332">Bona per se
        <lb ed="#V" n="78"/>metipsa amanda sunt: et non penis compel
        <lb ed="#V" n="79" break="no"/>lentibus exequenda. Nam qui propterea
        <lb ed="#V" n="80"/>bona facit: quia tormentorum mala metuit
        <lb ed="#V" n="81"/>vult non esse quod metuit vt audenter commit
        <lb ed="#V" n="82"/>tat illicita.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d78990-d1e346">
               <lb ed="#V" n="83"/>
            <ref>¶ Isydorus in synonima solliloquiorum: libro
        <lb ed="#V" n="84"/>2. c. 45.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d78990-Qd1e350">A subditis venerari magisquam time
        <lb ed="#V" n="85" break="no"/>ri stude. Snbiecti plus te reuereantur quam
        <lb ed="#V" n="86"/>metuant: plus tibi officio dilectionis quam con
        <lb ed="#V" n="87" break="no"/>ditionis necessitate adhereant. Talem te red
        <lb ed="#V" n="88"/>de subiectis vt magis ameris quam timearis.
        <lb ed="#V" n="89"/>Odium timor affert. Fidem metus tollit.
        <lb ed="#V" n="90"/>Non sis terribilis in subditis: sic his domi <!--237.xml-->
        <pb ed="#V" n="99-v"/>
                  <cb ed="#V" n="a"/>
                  <lb ed="#V" n="1"/>nare vt delectent seruire. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d78990-d1e377">
               <lb ed="#V" n="2"/>
            <ref>¶ Uersificator fabularum esopi. 32. f.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d78990-Qd1e381">Cum ti
        <lb ed="#V" n="3" break="no"/>mor in pacto sedit: promissa timore
        <lb ed="#V" n="4"/>Arent: nil fidei verba timentis habent.</quote>
            </p>
    
         </div>
